HEADWORD: Osteoplastic
<hw>Os`te*o*plas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Osteo-</ets> + <ets>-plastic</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Producing bone; <as>as,
<ex>osteoplastic</ex> cells</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
replacement of bone; <as>as, an <ex>osteoplastic</ex>
operation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osteoplasty</ent>⟦br⟧
